pageContext.claim: “Schiff didn't want to have the whistleblower anymore because nobody thought I was going to release the phone call.”
pageContext.analysis: Rep. Adam Schiff actually said that security concerns -- stemming in part from Trump's relentless public attacks on the whistleblower -- led to a change of plans. The House intelligence committee at first planned to take testimony from the whistleblower but later canceled those plans.
